sql:
SELECT DISTINCT title, imdb_rating 
FROM episodes 
WHERE imdb_rating > 9.2;

SELECT title
FROM episodes
WHERE id NOT IN (SELECT episode_id FROM viewership WHERE us_viewers_in_millions <= 1);

SELECT us_viewers_in_millions
FROM episodes
WHERE season = 4 AND views = (SELECT MAX(views) FROM episodes WHERE season = 4);

SELECT title, season
FROM episodes
WHERE imdb_rating > (SELECT AVG(imdb_rating) FROM episodes);

external_knowledge:
- The "journey" metaphorically represents the progression of seasons and episodes; 
- "Audience appreciation" is symbolized by "viewership in millions"; 
- "Critical acclaim" is symbolized by "IMDb rating"; 
- "Rising tide" metaphorically implies the cumulative increase in viewership over time;
- "Echo of ratings reverberated" metaphorically suggests the cumulative impact of ratings over the episodes.

sql:
SELECT title, us_viewers_in_millions
FROM episodes
WHERE us_viewers_in_millions = (
  SELECT MAX(us_viewers_in_millions)
  FROM episodes
);

external_knowledge:
'Popular seasons' and 'significant attention' refer to episodes that meet the criteria of having more than 10 million US viewers and over 1 million views, or an average US viewer count over 10 million.;
The term 'impressive numbers' in the context of 'US viewers and general views' indicates a threshold of 10 million and 1 million respectively.;
'Maintaining a high average viewer count' is defined as an average US viewer count exceeding 10 million.
